net.hudup.core.evaluate

Class Metrics

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.evaluate.Metrics
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Metrics
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This Metrics class manages a list of Metric (s). It uses @metric wrapper represented by MetricWrapper for sophisticated management tasks. The most important method of Metrics is recalc(String, int, Class, Object[]) method which is responsible for re-calculating all metrics in metric wrappers of this Metrics. Evaluator often calls recalc(String, int, Class, Object[]) method to re-calculate all metrics after each iteration of algorithm execution.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

    • Field Detail

      • metricWrapperList

        protected java.util.List<MetricWrapper> metricWrapperList
        List of metric wrappers. Each metric wrapper holds an internal metric and so such internal metric is the real one. The reason of this structure because metric wrapper contains additional information for complex task. So it is possible to consider metric wrappers as normal metrics. Note a metric wrapper inherits an abstract metric which is also a metric.

      • datasetUriMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,xURI> datasetUriMap
        A map of many dataset URI (s). Each dataset URI points to where to store such dataset. Each dataset URI is associated with a key which is known as identifier (ID) of the dataset.

      • recalc

        public Metrics recalc(java.lang.String algName,
                      int datasetId,
                      java.lang.Class<? extends Metric> metricClass,
                      java.lang.Object[] params)
        Re-calculating all metrics in metric wrappers of this Metrics. Evaluator often calls this method to re-calculate all metrics after each iteration of algorithm execution.
        Parameters:
        algName - only metric wrappers (of this Metrics) having the same algorithm specified by this input parameter are calculated.
        datasetId - only metric wrappers (of this Metrics) having the same dataset identifier specified by this input parameter are calculated.
        metricClass - if not null, only metric wrappers (of this Metrics) having the same class specified by the input parameter metricClass are calculated.
        params - input parameters of method MetricWrapper.recalc(Object...) for re-calculating metrics.
        Returns:
        current computed Metrics.

      • recalc

        public Metrics recalc(java.lang.String algName,
                      int datasetId,
                      java.lang.Object[] params)
        This method calls the method recalc(String, int, Class, Object[]) to re-calculate all metrics in metric wrappers of this Metrics.
        Parameters:
        algName - only metric wrappers (of this Metrics) having the same algorithm specified by this input parameter are calculated.
        datasetId - only metric wrappers (of this Metrics) having the same dataset identifier specified by this input parameter are calculated.
        params - input parameters of method MetricWrapper.recalc(Object...) for re-calculating metrics.
        Returns:
        current computed Metrics.
